How to verify that a method is **not** called on an object&#39;s dependency?

For example:

    public interface Dependency {
        void someMethod();
    }
    
    public class Foo {
        public bar(final Dependency d) {
            ...
        }
    }
    
With the Foo test:

    public class FooTest {
